gomodel:SYNGO_5302  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3, 5, 6: FGF22 coimmunoprecipitated with SDC2 in neuro2A cells and overexpressed FGF22 was localized to dendritic spines in hippocampal neurons (localization seems most concentrated at the spine tip). Postsynaptic localization was strongly reduced upon SDC2 shRNA knockdown.\n\nFigure 4: FGF22 interacts with SDC2 via heparan sulfate conjugates and contributes to SDC2-induced presynaptic differentiation.\n\nFigure 8: authors propose a model where FGF22 is attached to SDC2 (which is at the PSD membrane) and released from there to act on presynaptic receptors.. Experimental description: M&M:\n\"Hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18-19 SD rat embryos were cultured and transfected as previously described\"\n\n\"SDC2, SDC2ΔC2, SDC2 RNAi knockdown, FGF22-mCherry, FGF22-GFP and FGF22 RNAi knockdown constructs have been previously described (Umemori et al.24; Lin et al.18; Terauchi et al.25; Terauchi et al.26)\"\n\nReference PMID:20505669 confirms these are mouse sequences; \"Expression plasmids for FGF22-EGFP and FGF7-DsRed were generated by subcloning the full-length mouse fgf22 or fgf7 cDNA (minus the stop codon) into the NheI-XhoI or EcoRI-ApaI sites of pEGFP-N1 or pDsRed2-N1 (Clontech) in frame.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5302" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

